# Niyi Builder — AI Notes

When creating or modifying anything in this repo, follow these principles.
Add new items here as the project evolves.

## 1. Gutenberg is the source of truth

Post content is **native Gutenberg block markup** in the database — not shortcodes, not plugin-only blobs, not JSON.

- **Layout JSON** (`BuilderDocument`) is an editing/runtime representation only.
- **Gutenberg block comments** (`<!-- wp:... -->`) are canonical for storage.
- **Serializer** (`packages/serializer`) is the boundary: internal JSON ↔ Gutenberg markup must round-trip with **no data loss**.
- **Visual editor** previews and edits the document tree; save/load always flows through the serializer to Gutenberg.

## 2. Use core Gutenberg blocks only — no `niyi/*` blocks

**Do not register or emit custom `wp:niyi/*` blocks.** We will not create plugin-owned block types.

Serialize and deserialize using **WordPress core (default) blocks** only, e.g.:

| Builder concept | Gutenberg target (examples) |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| Container       | `core/group`                |
| Grid / columns  | `core/columns`, `core/column` |
| Spacer          | `core/spacer`               |
| Heading         | `core/heading`              |
| Text            | `core/paragraph`            |
| Button          | `core/button`               |
| Image           | `core/image`                |
| Video           | `core/embed` / `core/video` |

- **Native attrs first** — map builder fields to Gutenberg block JSON when core provides an equivalent (`layout`, `style`, `level`, `url`, `height`, …).
- **`niyi` overflow** — only attrs with **no** Gutenberg equivalent (responsive tablet/mobile overflow, `variant`, `typography`, `columns` count, etc.) go under `attrs.niyi`.
- **Parse** merges native extraction + `niyi`; responsive keys deep-merge.
- **No `block.json`**, PHP render callbacks, or `register_block_type` for `niyi/*` in this plugin.
- **Goal:** deactivate the plugin → content stays fully readable and editable in Gutenberg with zero custom blocks.

> **Note:** Layout JSON uses `core/*` block type names aligned with Gutenberg. The serializer emits standard block comments (`<!-- wp:group -->`, not `<!-- wp:core/group -->`).

### Do

- Store builder-specific fields in `attrs.niyi` on core blocks; keep native attrs minimal.
- Validate documents before serialize/parse; keep round-trip tests green.
- When unsure, prefer `niyi` for anything the builder owns (responsive values, variants, typography).

### Don't

- Add new `niyi/*` block types, namespaces, or registrations.
- Store layout JSON as post content or as the canonical saved format.
- Introduce editor-only fields that cannot round-trip to core block attributes.
